Install MongoDB on Ubuntu:
  http://docs.mongodb.org/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/
  
MongoDB Version:
  2.6.5
  
MongoDB Startup Command:
  sudo mongod --dbpath /opt/mongodb/data/db --logpath /opt/mongodb/data/log/mongodb.log --logappend &
  	If "Unclean shutdown detected." warning exists, remove this file: /opt/mongodb/data/db/mongod.lock

MonjaDB (MongoDB GUI client tool in Eclipse): 
  http://www.jumperz.net/index.php?i=2&a=0&b=9

MongoDB JDBC
https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-java-driver/downloads
download and add mongo-2.10.1.jar to buildpath

Netty Version: 
  4.0.23
  add netty-all-4.0.23.Final-source.jar and netty-all-4.0.23.Final.jar to buildPath

Netty Example:
  https://github.com/netty/netty/tree/master/example/src/main/java/io/netty/example/http
  
ProtoBuf version:
2.5.0
add protobuf-java-2.5.0.jar to buildpath
  
GitHub Tutorial:
  http://docs.joomla.org/Working_with_Git_and_Eclipse

Connect remote MongoDB:
  http://ghosttx.com/2012/03/how-to-connect-to-a-remote-mongodb-server-with-mongohub-for-mac/
